  <Name>k__BackingField: Hosea
  fancyName: 
  nickname: hos
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Family of Hosea'
      title: The Family of Hosea
      number: 1
      content: The word of the Lord that came to Hosea the son of Beeri, in the days
        of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and  Hezekiah, kings of Judah, and in the days of
        Jeroboam the son of Joash, king of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When the Lord began to speak by Hosea, the Lord said to Hosea:\u201CGo,
        take yourself a wife of harlotryAnd children of harlotry,For the land has
        committed great harlotryBy  departing from the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So he went and took Gomer the daughter of Diblaim, and she conceived
        and bore him a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the Lord said to him:\u201CCall his name Jezreel,For in a little
        whileI will avenge the bloodshed of Jezreel on the house of Jehu,And bring
        an end to the kingdom of the house of Israel."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "It shall come to pass in that dayThat I will break the bow of Israel
        in the Valley of Jezreel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And she conceived again and bore a daughter. Then God said to him:\u201CCall
        her name Lo-Ruhamah,For I will no longer have mercy on the house of Israel,But
        I will utterly take them away."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Yet I will have mercy on the house of Judah,Will save them by the
        Lord their God,And will not save them by bow,Nor by sword or battle,By horses
        or horsemen.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now when she had weaned Lo-Ruhamah, she conceived and bore a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Restoration of Israel'
      title: The Restoration of Israel
      number: 9
      content: "Then God said:\u201CCall his name Lo-Ammi,For you are not My people,And
        I will not be your God."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CYet the number of the children of IsraelShall be as the sand
        of the sea,Which cannot be measured or numbered.And it shall come to passIn
        the place where it was said to them,\u2018You are not My people,\u2019There
        it shall be said to them,\u2018You  are  sons of the living God.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Then the children of Judah and the children of IsraelShall be gathered
        together,And appoint for themselves one head;And they shall come up out of
        the land,For great will  be the day of Jezreel!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Unfaithful People"
      title: "God\u2019s Unfaithful People"
      number: 1
      content: "Say to your brethren, \u2018My people,\u2019And to your sisters,
        \u2018Mercy is  shown.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CBring charges against your mother, bring charges;For she is
        not My wife, nor am I her Husband!Let her put away her harlotries from her
        sight,And her adulteries from between her breasts;"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Lest I strip her nakedAnd expose her, as in the day she was born,And
        make her like a wilderness,And set her like a dry land,And slay her with
        thirst.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI will not have mercy on her children,For they are the children
        of harlotry."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For their mother has played the harlot;She who conceived them has
        behaved shamefully.For she said, \u2018I will go after my lovers,Who give
        me my bread and my water,My wool and my linen,My oil and my drink.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CTherefore, behold,I will hedge up your way with thorns,And
        wall her in,So that she cannot find her paths."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "She will chase her lovers,But not overtake them;Yes, she will seek
        them, but not find them.Then she will say,\u2018I will go and return to my
        first husband,For then it  was better for me than now.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For she did not knowThat I gave her grain, new wine, and oil,And
        multiplied her silver and gold\u2014Which they prepared for Baal."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CTherefore I will return and take awayMy grain in its timeAnd
        My new wine in its season,And will take back My wool and My linen,Given to
        cover her nakedness."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Now I will uncover her lewdness in the sight of her lovers,And no
        one shall deliver her from My hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "I will also cause all her mirth to cease,Her feast days,Her New Moons,Her
        Sabbaths\u2014All her appointed feasts."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CAnd I will destroy her vines and her fig trees,Of which she
        has said,\u2018These are my wages that my lovers have given me.\u2019So I
        will make them a forest,And the beasts of the field shall eat them."
      comments: []
    - name: "13: God\u2019s Mercy on His People"
      title: "God\u2019s Mercy on His People"
      number: 13
      content: "I will punish herFor the days of the Baals to which she burned incense.She
        decked herself with her earrings and jewelry,And went after her lovers;But
        Me she forgot,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CTherefore, behold, I will allure her,Will bring her into the
        wilderness,And speak comfort to her."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: I will give her her vineyards from there,And the Valley of Achor as
        a door of hope;She shall sing there,As in the days of her youth,As in the
        day when she came up from the land of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CAnd it shall be, in that day,\u201DSays the Lord,\u201CThat
        you will call Me \u2018My Husband,\u2019And no longer call Me \u2018My Master,\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: For I will take from her mouth the names of the Baals,And they shall
        be remembered by their name no more.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: In that day I will make a covenant for themWith the beasts of the
        field,With the birds of the air,And with the creeping things of the ground.Bow
        and sword of battle I will shatter from the earth,To make them lie down safely.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CI will betroth you to Me forever;Yes, I will betroth you to
        MeIn righteousness and justice,In lovingkindness and mercy;"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: I will betroth you to Me in faithfulness,And you shall know the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CIt shall come to pass in that dayThat  I will answer,\u201D
        says the Lord;\u201CI will answer the heavens,And they shall answer the earth."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: The earth shall answerWith grain,With new wine,And with oil;They shall
        answer Jezreel.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then I will sow her for Myself in the earth,And I will have mercy
        on her  who  had not obtained mercy;Then I will say to those  who  were not
        My people,\u2018You are My people!\u2019And they shall say, \u2018You are
        my God!\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Will Return to God'
      title: Israel Will Return to God
      number: 1
      content: "Then the Lord said to me, \u201CGo again, love a woman who  is loved
        by a lover and is committing adultery, just like the love of the Lord for
        the children of Israel, who look to other gods and love the raisin cakes
        of  the  pagans.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I bought her for myself for fifteen shekels of silver, and one
        and one-half homers of barley. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And I said to her, \u201CYou shall stay with me many days; you shall
        not play the harlot, nor shall you have a man\u2014so, too, will I be toward
        you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the children of Israel shall abide many days without king or
        prince, without sacrifice or sacred pillar, without ephod or teraphim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Afterward the children of Israel shall return and seek the Lord their
        God and David their king. They shall fear the Lord and His goodness in the
        latter days.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Charge Against Israel"
      title: "God\u2019s Charge Against Israel"
      number: 1
      content: "Hear the word of the Lord,You children of Israel,For the Lord  brings
        a charge against the inhabitants of the land:\u201CThere is no truth or mercyOr
        knowledge of God in the land."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: By swearing and lying,Killing and stealing and committing adultery,They
        break all restraint,With bloodshed upon bloodshed.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Therefore the land will mourn;And everyone who dwells there will waste
        awayWith the beasts of the fieldAnd the birds of the air;Even the fish of
        the sea will be taken away.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CNow let no man contend, or rebuke another;For your people are
        like those who contend with the priest."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Therefore you shall stumble in the day;The prophet also shall stumble
        with you in the night;And I will destroy your mother.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: My people are destroyed for lack of knowledge.Because you have rejected
        knowledge,I also will reject you from being priest for Me;Because you have
        forgotten the law of your God,I also will forget your children.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThe more they increased,The more they sinned against Me;I will
        change their glory into shame."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: They eat up the sin of My people;They set their heart on their iniquity.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And it shall be: like people, like priest.So I will punish them for
        their ways,And reward them for their deeds.'
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Idolatry of Israel'
      title: The Idolatry of Israel
      number: 10
      content: For they shall eat, but not have enough;They shall commit harlotry,
        but not increase;Because they have ceased obeying the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CHarlotry, wine, and new wine enslave the heart."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: My people ask counsel from their wooden idols,And their staff informs
        them.For the spirit of harlotry has caused them to stray,And they have played
        the harlot against their God.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: They offer sacrifices on the mountaintops,And burn incense on the
        hills,Under oaks, poplars, and terebinths,Because their shade is good.Therefore
        your daughters commit harlotry,And your brides commit adultery.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CI will not punish your daughters when they commit harlotry,Nor
        your brides when they commit adultery;For the  men themselves go apart with
        harlots,And offer sacrifices with a ritual harlot.Therefore people who do
        not understand will be trampled."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThough you, Israel, play the harlot,Let not Judah offend.Do
        not come up to Gilgal,Nor go up to Beth Aven,Nor swear an oath, saying, \u2018As
        the Lord lives\u2019\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CFor Israel is stubbornLike a stubborn calf;Now the Lord will
        let them forageLike a lamb in open country."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CEphraim is joined to idols,Let him alone."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Their drink is rebellion,They commit harlotry continually.Her rulers
        dearly love dishonor.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The wind has wrapped her up in its wings,And they shall be ashamed
        because of their sacrifices.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Impending Judgment on Israel and Judah'
      title: Impending Judgment on Israel and Judah
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CHear this, O priests!Take heed, O house of Israel!Give ear,
        O house of the king!For yours is the judgment,Because you have been a snare
        to MizpahAnd a net spread on Tabor."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The revolters are deeply involved in slaughter,Though I rebuke them
        all.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: I know Ephraim,And Israel is not hidden from Me;For now, O Ephraim,
        you commit harlotry;Israel is defiled.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CThey do not direct their deedsToward turning to their God,For
        the spirit of harlotry is in their midst,And they do not know the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The pride of Israel testifies to his face;Therefore Israel and Ephraim
        stumble in their iniquity;Judah also stumbles with them.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CWith their flocks and herdsThey shall go to seek the Lord,But
        they will not find Him;He has withdrawn Himself from them."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: They have dealt treacherously with the Lord,For they have begotten
        pagan children.Now a New Moon shall devour them and their heritage.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBlow the ram\u2019s horn in Gibeah,The trumpet in Ramah!Cry
        aloud at  Beth Aven,\u2018Look behind you, O Benjamin!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Ephraim shall be desolate in the day of rebuke;Among the tribes of
        Israel I make known what is sure.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThe princes of Judah are like those who remove a landmark;I
        will pour out My wrath on them like water."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Ephraim is oppressed and broken in judgment,Because he willingly walked
        by human precept.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Therefore I will  be to Ephraim like a moth,And to the house of Judah
        like rottenness.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CWhen Ephraim saw his sickness,And Judah saw his wound,Then
        Ephraim went to AssyriaAnd sent to King Jareb;Yet he cannot cure you,Nor
        heal you of your wound."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: For I will  be like a lion to Ephraim,And like a young lion to the
        house of Judah.I, even I, will tear them and go away;I will take them away,
        and no one shall rescue.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I will return again to My placeTill they acknowledge their offense.Then
        they will seek My face;In their affliction they will earnestly seek Me.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Call to Repentance'
      title: A Call to Repentance
      number: 1
      content: Come, and let us return to the Lord;For He has torn, but He will heal
        us;He has stricken, but He will bind us up.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: After two days He will revive us;On the third day He will raise us
        up,That we may live in His sight.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: Impenitence of Israel and Judah'
      title: Impenitence of Israel and Judah
      number: 3
      content: Let us know,Let us pursue the knowledge of the Lord.His going forth
        is established as the morning;He will come to us like the rain,Like the latter
        and former rain to the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CO Ephraim, what shall I do to you?O Judah, what shall I do
        to you?For your faithfulness is like a morning cloud,And like the early dew
        it goes away."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Therefore I have hewn them by the prophets,I have slain them by the
        words of My mouth;And your judgments are  like light that goes forth.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For I desire mercy and not sacrifice,And the knowledge of God more
        than burnt offerings.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBut like men they transgressed the covenant;There they dealt
        treacherously with Me."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Gilead is a city of evildoersAnd defiled with blood.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: As bands of robbers lie in wait for a man,So the company of priests
        murder on the way to Shechem;Surely they commit lewdness.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: I have seen a horrible thing in the house of Israel:There is the harlotry
        of Ephraim;Israel is defiled.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Also, O Judah, a harvest is appointed for you,When I return the captives
        of My people.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CWhen I would have healed Israel,Then the iniquity of Ephraim
        was uncovered,And the wickedness of Samaria.For they have committed fraud;A
        thief comes in;A band of robbers takes spoil outside."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: They do not consider in their heartsThat  I remember all their wickedness;Now
        their own deeds have surrounded them;They are before My face.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: They make a king glad with their wickedness,And princes with their
        lies.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CThey  are all adulterers.Like an oven heated by a baker\u2014He
        ceases stirring the  fire after kneading the dough,Until it is leavened."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: In the day of our kingPrinces have made him sick, inflamed with wine;He
        stretched out his hand with scoffers.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: They prepare their heart like an oven,While they lie in wait;Their
        baker sleeps all night;In the morning it burns like a flaming fire.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: They are all hot, like an oven,And have devoured their judges;All
        their kings have fallen.None among them calls upon Me.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CEphraim has mixed himself among the peoples;Ephraim is a cake
        unturned."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Aliens have devoured his strength,But he does not know it;Yes, gray
        hairs are here and there on him,Yet he does not know it.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Futile Reliance on the Nations'
      title: Futile Reliance on the Nations
      number: 10
      content: And the pride of Israel testifies to his face,But they do not return
        to the Lord their God,Nor seek Him for all this.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CEphraim also is like a silly dove, without sense\u2014They
        call to Egypt,They go to Assyria."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Wherever they go, I will spread My net on them;I will bring them down
        like birds of the air;I will chastise themAccording to what their congregation
        has heard.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CWoe to them, for they have fled from Me!Destruction to them,Because
        they have transgressed against Me!Though I redeemed them,Yet they have spoken
        lies against Me."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They did not cry out to Me with their heartWhen they wailed upon
        their beds.\u201CThey assemble together for grain and new wine,They rebel
        against Me;"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Though I disciplined and strengthened their arms,Yet they devise evil
        against Me;
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: They return, but not to the Most High;They are like a treacherous
        bow.Their princes shall fall by the swordFor the cursings of their tongue.This
        shall  be their derision in the land of Egypt.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Apostasy of Israel'
      title: The Apostasy of Israel
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CSet the trumpet to your mouth!He  shall  come  like an eagle
        against the house of the Lord,Because they have transgressed My covenantAnd
        rebelled against My law."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Israel will cry to Me,\u2018My God, we know You!\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Israel has rejected the good;The enemy will pursue him.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CThey set up kings, but not by Me;They made princes, but I did
        not acknowledge them.From their silver and goldThey made idols for themselves\u2014That
        they might be cut off."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Your calf is rejected, O Samaria!My anger is aroused against them\u2014How
        long until they attain to innocence?"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For from Israel is even this:A workman made it, and it is not God;But
        the calf of Samaria shall be broken to pieces.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThey sow the wind,And reap the whirlwind.The stalk has no bud;It
        shall never produce meal.If it should produce,Aliens would swallow it up."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Israel is swallowed up;Now they are among the GentilesLike a vessel
        in which is no pleasure.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: For they have gone up to Assyria,Like  a wild donkey alone by itself;Ephraim
        has hired lovers.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Yes, though they have hired among the nations,Now I will gather them;And
        they shall sorrow a little,Because of the burden of the king of princes.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBecause Ephraim has made many altars for sin,They have become
        for him altars for sinning."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: I have written for him the great things of My law,But they were considered
        a strange thing.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: For the sacrifices of My offerings they sacrifice flesh and eat it,But
        the Lord does not accept them.Now He will remember their iniquity and punish
        their sins.They shall return to Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CFor Israel has forgotten his Maker,And has built temples;Judah
        also has multiplied fortified cities;But I will send fire upon his cities,And
        it shall devour his palaces.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Judgment of Israel\u2019s Sin"
      title: "Judgment of Israel\u2019s Sin"
      number: 1
      content: Do not rejoice, O Israel, with joy like other peoples,For you have
        played the harlot against your God.You have made love for  hire on every
        threshing floor.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The threshing floor and the winepressShall not feed them,And the new
        wine shall fail in her.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They shall not dwell in the Lord\u2019s land,But Ephraim shall return
        to Egypt,And shall eat unclean things in Assyria."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: They shall not offer wine offerings to the Lord,Nor shall their sacrifices
        be pleasing to Him.It  shall  be like bread of mourners to them;All who eat
        it shall be defiled.For their bread shall  be for their own life;It shall
        not come into the house of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: What will you do in the appointed day,And in the day of the feast
        of the Lord?
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For indeed they are gone because of destruction.Egypt shall gather
        them up;Memphis shall bury them.Nettles shall possess their valuables of
        silver;Thorns shall  be in their tents.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The days of punishment have come;The days of recompense have come.Israel
        knows!The prophet is a fool,The spiritual man is insane,Because of the greatness
        of your iniquity and great enmity.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The watchman of Ephraim is with my God;But the prophet is a fowler\u2019s
        snare in all his ways\u2014Enmity in the house of his God."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: They are deeply corrupted,As in the days of Gibeah.He will remember
        their iniquity;He will punish their sins.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CI found IsraelLike grapes in the wilderness;I saw your fathersAs
        the firstfruits on the fig tree in its first season.But they went to Baal
        Peor,And separated themselves to  that shame;They became an abomination like
        the thing they loved."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "As  for Ephraim, their glory shall fly away like a bird\u2014No birth,
        no pregnancy, and no conception!"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Though they bring up their children,Yet I will bereave them to the
        last man.Yes, woe to them when I depart from them!
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Just as I saw Ephraim like Tyre, planted in a pleasant place,So Ephraim
        will bring out his children to the murderer.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Give them, O Lord\u2014What will You give?Give them a miscarrying
        wombAnd dry breasts!"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAll their wickedness is in Gilgal,For there I hated them.Because
        of the evil of their deedsI will drive them from My house;I will love them
        no more.All their princes are rebellious."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Ephraim is stricken,Their root is dried up;They shall bear no fruit.Yes,
        were they to bear children,I would kill the darlings of their womb.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: My God will cast them away,Because they did not obey Him;And they
        shall be wanderers among the nations.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Sin and Captivity"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Sin and Captivity"
      number: 1
      content: Israel empties his vine;He brings forth fruit for himself.According
        to the multitude of his fruitHe has increased the altars;According to the
        bounty of his landThey have embellished his  sacred pillars.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Their heart is divided;Now they are held guilty.He will break down
        their altars;He will ruin their sacred pillars.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For now they say,\u201CWe have no king,Because we did not fear the
        Lord.And as for a king, what would he do for us?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: They have spoken words,Swearing falsely in making a covenant.Thus
        judgment springs up like hemlock in the furrows of the field.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The inhabitants of Samaria fearBecause of the calf of Beth Aven.For
        its people mourn for it,And its priests shriek for it\u2014Because its glory
        has departed from it."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The  idol also shall be carried to AssyriaAs a present for King Jareb.Ephraim
        shall receive shame,And Israel shall be ashamed of his own counsel.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: As  for Samaria, her king is cut offLike a twig on the water.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Also the high places of Aven, the sin of Israel,Shall be destroyed.The
        thorn and thistle shall grow on their altars;They shall say to the mountains,
        \u201CCover us!\u201DAnd to the hills, \u201CFall on us!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CO Israel, you have sinned from the days of Gibeah;There they
        stood.The battle in Gibeah against the children of iniquityDid not overtake
        them."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: When it  is My desire, I will chasten them.Peoples shall be gathered
        against themWhen I bind them for their two transgressions.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Ephraim is  a trained heiferThat loves to thresh grain;But I harnessed
        her fair neck,I will make Ephraim pull a  plow.Judah shall plow;Jacob shall
        break his clods.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Sow for yourselves righteousness;Reap in mercy;Break up your fallow
        ground,For it  is time to seek the Lord,Till He comes and rains righteousness
        on you.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: You have plowed wickedness;You have reaped iniquity.You have eaten
        the fruit of lies,Because you trusted in your own way,In the multitude of
        your mighty men.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore tumult shall arise among your people,And all your fortresses
        shall be plunderedAs Shalman plundered Beth Arbel in the day of battle\u2014A
        mother dashed in pieces upon her children."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Thus it shall be done to you, O Bethel,Because of your great wickedness.At
        dawn the king of IsraelShall be cut off utterly.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Continuing Love for Israel"
      title: "God\u2019s Continuing Love for Israel"
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CWhen Israel was a child, I loved him,And out of Egypt I called
        My son."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: As they called them,So they went from them;They sacrificed to the
        Baals,And burned incense to carved images.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI taught Ephraim to walk,Taking them by their arms;But they
        did not know that I healed them."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: I drew them with gentle cords,With bands of love,And I was to them
        as those who take the yoke from their neck.I stooped and fed them.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CHe shall not return to the land of Egypt;But the Assyrian shall
        be his king,Because they refused to repent."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And the sword shall slash in his cities,Devour his districts,And consume
        them,Because of their own counsels.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: My people are bent on backsliding from Me.Though they call to the
        Most High,None at all exalt Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CHow can I give you up, Ephraim?How can I hand you over, Israel?How
        can I make you like Admah?How can I set you like Zeboiim?My heart churns
        within Me;My sympathy is stirred."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: I will not execute the fierceness of My anger;I will not again destroy
        Ephraim.For I am God, and not man,The Holy One in your midst;And I will not
        come with terror.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThey shall walk after the Lord.He will roar like a lion.When
        He roars,Then His sons shall come trembling from the west;"
      comments: []
    - name: "11: God\u2019s Charge Against Ephraim"
      title: "God\u2019s Charge Against Ephraim"
      number: 11
      content: "They shall come trembling like a bird from Egypt,Like a dove from
        the land of Assyria.And I will let them dwell in their houses,\u201DSays
        the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CEphraim has encircled Me with lies,And the house of Israel
        with deceit;But Judah still walks with God,Even with the Holy One who  is
        faithful."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "\u201CEphraim feeds on the wind,And pursues the east wind;He daily
        increases lies and desolation.Also they make a covenant with the Assyrians,And
        oil is carried to Egypt."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThe  Lord also brings a charge against Judah,And will punish
        Jacob according to his ways;According to his deeds He will recompense him."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: He took his brother by the heel in the womb,And in his strength he
        struggled with God.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Yes, he struggled with the Angel and prevailed;He wept, and sought
        favor from Him.He found Him in  Bethel,And there He spoke to us\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: That is, the Lord God of hosts.The Lord  is His memorable name.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: So you, by the  help  of your God, return;Observe mercy and justice,And
        wait on your God continually.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CA cunning Canaanite!Deceitful scales are in his hand;He loves
        to oppress."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Ephraim said,\u2018Surely I have become rich,I have found wealth
        for myself;In all my laborsThey shall find in me no iniquity that is sin.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CBut I am the Lord your God,Ever since the land of Egypt;I will
        again make you dwell in tents,As in the days of the appointed feast."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I have also spoken by the prophets,And have multiplied visions;I
        have given symbols through the witness of the prophets.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Though Gilead has idols\u2014Surely they are vanity\u2014Though they
        sacrifice bulls in Gilgal,Indeed their altars shall  be heaps in the furrows
        of the field."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Jacob fled to the country of Syria;Israel served for a spouse,And
        for a wife he tended sheep.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: By a prophet the Lord brought Israel out of Egypt,And by a prophet
        he was preserved.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Ephraim provoked Him to anger most bitterly;Therefore his Lord will
        leave the guilt of his bloodshed upon him,And return his reproach upon him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Relentless Judgment on Israel'
      title: Relentless Judgment on Israel
      number: 1
      content: When Ephraim spoke, trembling,He exalted himself in Israel;But when
        he offended through Baal worship, he died.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now they sin more and more,And have made for themselves molded images,Idols
        of their silver, according to their skill;All of it is the work of craftsmen.They
        say of them,\u201CLet the men who sacrifice kiss the calves!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Therefore they shall be like the morning cloudAnd like the early dew
        that passes away,Like chaff blown off from a threshing floorAnd like smoke
        from a chimney.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYet I am the Lord your GodEver since the land of Egypt,And
        you shall know no God but Me;For there  is no savior besides Me."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: I knew you in the wilderness,In the land of great drought.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: When they had pasture, they were filled;They were filled and their
        heart was exalted;Therefore they forgot Me.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CSo I will be to them like a lion;Like a leopard by the road
        I will lurk;"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: I will meet them like a bear deprived of  her  cubs;I will tear open
        their rib cage,And there I will devour them like a lion.The wild beast shall
        tear them.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CO Israel, you are destroyed,But your help is from Me."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I will be your King;Where is  any  other,That he may save you in
        all your cities?And your judges to whom you said,\u2018Give me a king and
        princes\u2019?"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: I gave you a king in My anger,And took him away in My wrath.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CThe iniquity of Ephraim is bound up;His sin is stored up."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The sorrows of a woman in childbirth shall come upon him.He is an
        unwise son,For he should not stay long where children are born.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CI will ransom them from the power of the grave;I will redeem
        them from death.O Death, I will be your plagues!O Grave, I will be your destruction!Pity
        is hidden from My eyes.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Though he is fruitful among his brethren,An east wind shall come;The
        wind of the Lord shall come up from the wilderness.Then his spring shall
        become dry,And his fountain shall be dried up.He shall plunder the treasury
        of every desirable prize.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Samaria is held guilty,For she has rebelled against her God.They shall
        fall by the sword,Their infants shall be dashed in pieces,And their women
        with child ripped open.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Restored at Last'
      title: Israel Restored at Last
      number: 1
      content: O Israel, return to the Lord your God,For you have stumbled because
        of your iniquity;
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Take words with you,And return to the Lord.Say to Him,\u201CTake
        away all iniquity;Receive us graciously,For we will offer the sacrifices
        of our lips."
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Assyria shall not save us,We will not ride on horses,Nor will we
        say anymore to the work of our hands, \u2018You  are our gods.\u2019For in
        You the fatherless finds mercy.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CI will heal their backsliding,I will love them freely,For My
        anger has turned away from him."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: I will be like the dew to Israel;He shall grow like the lily,And lengthen
        his roots like Lebanon.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: His branches shall spread;His beauty shall be like an olive tree,And
        his fragrance like Lebanon.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Those who dwell under his shadow shall return;They shall be revived
        like grain,And grow like a vine.Their scent shall  be like the wine of Lebanon.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CEphraim shall  say, \u2018What have I to do anymore with idols?\u2019I
        have heard and observed him.I am like a green cypress tree;Your fruit is
        found in Me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Who is wise?Let him understand these things.Who  is prudent?Let him
        know them.For the ways of the Lord  are right;The righteous walk in them,But
        transgressors stumble in them.
      comments: []
